527
00:37:58,748 --> 00:38:01,556
Ah, well we just happened to be...

528
00:38:02,498 --> 00:38:03,842
There goes the money.

529
00:38:08,213 --> 00:38:09,481
Money?

530
00:38:11,739 --> 00:38:15,157
Why don't we go
buy some clothes for now?

531
00:38:15,157 --> 00:38:16,438
Yes, let's do that.

532
00:38:28,978 --> 00:38:31,925
Oh, here. Take these.

533
00:38:31,925 --> 00:38:34,101
- Put on the underwear first.
- Thank you.

534
00:38:34,101 --> 00:38:35,773
I bought something for you too, Mi Yeon.

535
00:38:35,773 --> 00:38:38,128
That's not going to fit me.

536
00:38:38,128 --> 00:38:39,255
I'll keep it.

537
00:38:39,255 --> 00:38:41,302
Oh, there it is. Here.

538
00:38:41,302 --> 00:38:43,175
Choose something.
2,000 won to 10,000 won.

539
00:38:43,175 --> 00:38:45,619
Choose something,
Miss Kyung and Miss Park.

540
00:38:45,619 --> 00:38:47,376
- Make a choice.
- How's this?

541
00:38:47,376 --> 00:38:49,661
- Hm...
- How's this then?

542
00:38:49,661 --> 00:38:52,405
This kind of pattern
doesn't suit my style.

543
00:38:52,405 --> 00:38:54,867
Isn't there something
more intellectual or elegant?

544
00:38:54,867 --> 00:38:56,693
How is this?

545
00:38:56,693 --> 00:39:01,340
Isn't there something more monochrome,
trendy, and sporty in design?

546
00:39:01,340 --> 00:39:02,702
- What are you saying?
- What?

547
00:39:02,702 --> 00:39:04,880
Hey, you're not
in a position to be picky.

548
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:06,387
This guy is picky.

549
00:39:06,387 --> 00:39:08,170
Come on inside then.

550
00:39:08,170 --> 00:39:09,556
We have lots of elegance inside.

551
00:39:09,556 --> 00:39:11,097
- Come on in.
- Oh, really?

552
00:39:12,882 --> 00:39:14,260
What's wrong with these?

553
00:39:27,661 --> 00:39:28,735
What do you think?

554
00:39:28,735 --> 00:39:30,806
It's great, right?
There's a good feeling.

555
00:39:30,806 --> 00:39:34,443
This is monochrome and sporty?

556
00:39:34,443 --> 00:39:38,106
2017 intellectual trendy fashion.

557
00:39:38,106 --> 00:39:40,726
As long as you like it...

558
00:39:40,726 --> 00:39:43,007
I really like it a lot.

559
00:39:48,889 --> 00:39:50,168
No...

560
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:54,349
I just can't.

561
00:39:54,349 --> 00:39:57,434
Joon understands fashion.

562
00:39:57,434 --> 00:39:59,954
I'm hungry. Let's just go eat.

563
00:39:59,954 --> 00:40:02,052
Should we? What should we eat?

564
00:40:02,052 --> 00:40:03,853
Me! That thing.

565
00:40:03,853 --> 00:40:05,563
I want to eat that thing.

566
00:40:05,563 --> 00:40:06,956
That thing.

567
00:40:14,262 --> 00:40:19,143
This exquisite taste
that reaches the depths of my soul.

568
00:40:19,143 --> 00:40:22,065
Why do you have so much to say
about a 6,000 won rice stew?

569
00:40:22,065 --> 00:40:23,155
Hurry up and eat.

570
00:40:23,155 --> 00:40:24,885
- Let's eat, everyone.
- Let's eat.

571
00:40:24,885 --> 00:40:27,338
Wait, wait, wait!

572
00:40:27,338 --> 00:40:28,775
Where did you go?

573
00:40:28,775 --> 00:40:29,851
Well...

574
00:40:31,786 --> 00:40:33,949
Here. Eat this first.

575
00:40:35,210 --> 00:40:38,572
If you go into places like that,
you have to eat this once you come out.

576
00:40:38,572 --> 00:40:40,972
It's so that you can become a new person.

577
00:40:40,972 --> 00:40:44,434
Chew it up and eat it.
Then don't ever go near those places.

578
00:40:49,242 --> 00:40:50,693
Why aren't you eating it?

579
00:40:55,362 --> 00:40:58,871
Without meaning to,
I hid my identity.

580
00:40:59,789 --> 00:41:01,289
I caused trouble and I'm really...

581
00:41:07,126 --> 00:41:08,356
happy!

582
00:41:10,688 --> 00:41:12,126
My goodness.

583
00:41:12,126 --> 00:41:13,967
Oh gosh.

584
00:41:16,094 --> 00:41:17,257
Here.

585
00:41:39,885 --> 00:41:42,481
CEO Byun asked for me.

586
00:41:42,481 --> 00:41:45,547
He just kicked out Young Master Hyuk.

587
00:41:45,547 --> 00:41:49,949
- What?
- He kicked him out without even 10 won.

588
00:41:49,949 --> 00:41:51,811
The mood is not good.

589
00:41:51,811 --> 00:41:55,460
Do whatever the CEO tells you to.

590
00:41:55,460 --> 00:41:58,005
You need to bow down to him, okay?

591
00:42:03,005 --> 00:42:04,206
Goodness.

592
00:42:16,239 --> 00:42:20,050
Gosh, I told you to give it a rest.

593
00:42:20,050 --> 00:42:22,684
Did the world end?

594
00:42:22,684 --> 00:42:25,929
How could you do this, Honey?

595
00:42:25,929 --> 00:42:28,137
He doesn't have any money.

596
00:42:28,137 --> 00:42:32,204
You're setting him up
to go out and starve to death.

597
00:42:32,204 --> 00:42:37,501
How ignorant of you to kick
him out in the nude like that.

598
00:42:37,501 --> 00:42:39,184
Oh, my baby.

599
00:42:39,184 --> 00:42:42,032
Where is my Hyuk?

600
00:42:42,032 --> 00:42:44,371
You told me to give him wings.

601
00:42:48,061 --> 00:42:49,992
What do you mean by that?

602
00:42:51,572 --> 00:42:53,934
If he has wings, he'll fly.

603
00:42:56,342 --> 00:42:58,402
I don't know about a phoenix.

604
00:42:58,402 --> 00:43:03,143
But, we have to throw him out to find
out if he's a baby chick or an eagle.

605
00:43:04,193 --> 00:43:06,400
CEO, you have a guest.

606
00:43:06,402 --> 00:43:07,532
What?

607
00:43:12,739 --> 00:43:14,313
Is he planning something?

608
00:43:18,628 --> 00:43:24,458
Do you have any idea
where Hyuk might have gone?

609
00:43:24,458 --> 00:43:27,507
No, I'll look into it once I leave.

610
00:43:27,507 --> 00:43:31,777
Once you find out his location,
report to me right away.

611
00:43:33,849 --> 00:43:36,329
What is your plan?

612
00:43:36,329 --> 00:43:38,114
Keep him close by.

613
00:43:38,114 --> 00:43:41,896
Find out what he's doing and
what he's thinking.

614
00:43:41,896 --> 00:43:43,657
Give me detailed reports.

615
00:43:45,494 --> 00:43:47,655
<i>What could he be thinking?</i>

616
00:43:49,414 --> 00:43:53,677
Perhaps, he wanted it resolved
with as little talk as possible.

617
00:43:53,677 --> 00:43:59,148
If he wanted people to stop talking,
he should have handed Hyuk over.

618
00:44:00,505 --> 00:44:03,626
He's taking criticism from
the media and public.

619
00:44:03,626 --> 00:44:05,516
Why protect Hyuk through all that?

620
00:44:05,516 --> 00:44:07,885
There is criticism.

621
00:44:07,885 --> 00:44:10,637
But, the victim came forward
and vindicated Hyuk.

622
00:44:10,637 --> 00:44:12,398
Wouldn't that resolve
the misunderstanding?

623
00:44:17,873 --> 00:44:20,105
People don't want the truth.

624
00:44:21,523 --> 00:44:24,554
They want to see bad people be punished.

625
00:44:24,554 --> 00:44:28,693
So, it doesn't matter if
that person is really bad or not.

626
00:44:28,693 --> 00:44:30,782
The thing I'm curious about is...

627
00:44:30,782 --> 00:44:35,054
why would he save Hyuk and
not the company at this juncture?

628
00:44:35,054 --> 00:44:36,855
What was Father thinking?

629
00:44:38,628 --> 00:44:42,367
Are you asking me to monitor Hyuk?

630
00:44:42,367 --> 00:44:45,681
I just want to know something.

631
00:44:45,681 --> 00:44:49,981
So, report everything
about him directly to me.

632
00:44:54,028 --> 00:44:57,954
You'll report to me first
before you tell my father, right?

633
00:44:59,454 --> 00:45:02,269
Don't go to anyone else first.
Come directly to me.

634
00:45:03,869 --> 00:45:07,289
Let's filter out what
you report to the CEO.

635
00:45:10,985 --> 00:45:12,414
Yes, Chief.

636
00:45:14,420 --> 00:45:17,076
Be careful so people
don't start talking about it.

637
00:45:19,105 --> 00:45:20,416
I understand, CEO.

638
00:45:47,045 --> 00:45:49,567
Joon, how was I today?

639
00:45:49,567 --> 00:45:51,806
I look great on TV, don't I?

640
00:45:53,076 --> 00:45:56,005
Byun Hyuk who was
determined to reveal the truth.

641
00:45:56,005 --> 00:45:57,838
I confidently made my way
to the prosecutor.

642
00:45:57,840 --> 00:45:59,211
Wasn't I kind of cool?

643
00:45:59,211 --> 00:46:01,143
Did you go there to look cool?

644
00:46:01,143 --> 00:46:02,295
<i>I did.</i>

645
00:46:02,295 --> 00:46:05,114
You went in because you did
something wrong, so you had to go.

646
00:46:05,114 --> 00:46:08,284
Lots of people don't do
things that they should do.

647
00:46:08,284 --> 00:46:09,815
You don't believe my sincerity?

648
00:46:09,815 --> 00:46:12,815
I'm not the old me.
I've really changed.

649
00:46:12,815 --> 00:46:15,394
So what if you've changed?
What does that have to do with me?

650
00:46:15,394 --> 00:46:16,887
Why wouldn't it?

651
00:46:16,887 --> 00:46:20,798
Didn't you see the letter I left you?

652
00:46:20,798 --> 00:46:24,809
<i>Please, call me by my name,
which suits my color and fragrance.</i>

653
00:46:24,809 --> 00:46:26,280
<i>I will go to you.</i>

654
00:46:26,280 --> 00:46:27,902
Stop that.

655
00:46:27,902 --> 00:46:30,393
I have to go to work.
Go in by yourself.

656
00:46:39,804 --> 00:46:41,916
What? What is it?

657
00:46:43,096 --> 00:46:45,416
I don't know how this will sound to you.

658
00:46:51,742 --> 00:46:53,146
But, I have no bus money.

659
00:47:07,173 --> 00:47:08,266
Here.

660
00:47:15,195 --> 00:47:16,670
Work is hard, isn't it?

661
00:47:20,309 --> 00:47:24,471
Bow down when the wind blows and
take the rain when there's a storm.

662
00:47:25,920 --> 00:47:30,286
To stay on the higher ups'
good side, that's the best way.

663
00:47:40,288 --> 00:47:41,990
<i>He was on the street,
so I picked him up.</i>

664
00:47:41,990 --> 00:47:44,619
<i>I sent him to my place.
You go and take care of him.</i>

665
00:47:50,460 --> 00:47:51,661
This punk.

666
00:47:54,641 --> 00:47:56,621
- I need to go.
- Oh?

667
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:02,019
Make sure to behave well.

668
00:48:02,019 --> 00:48:05,188
Father, I'll take care of it.

669
00:48:05,188 --> 00:48:06,288
All right.

670
00:48:49,603 --> 00:48:51,199
Woo!

671
00:48:52,748 --> 00:48:54,347
I'm back.

672
00:48:54,347 --> 00:48:57,307
The paradise that I longed for.

673
00:48:59,519 --> 00:49:01,833
When is Joon coming home?

674
00:49:06,635 --> 00:49:08,960
You have very unique taste.

675
00:49:13,672 --> 00:49:16,536
Which brand is that, exactly?

676
00:49:20,186 --> 00:49:22,567
Who needs brand names?

677
00:49:22,567 --> 00:49:24,766
Once I wear it,
it becomes designer level.

678
00:49:29,987 --> 00:49:31,807
Thank you for before.

679
00:49:33,336 --> 00:49:35,385
I didn't do it to get your thanks.

680
00:49:35,385 --> 00:49:37,557
I only told the truth.

681
00:49:37,557 --> 00:49:39,206
Right? It was.

682
00:49:39,206 --> 00:49:40,871
The weather was bad that day.

683
00:49:40,871 --> 00:49:45,190
Nonetheless, I felt sexually harassed
from my point of view and that's a fact.

684
00:49:45,190 --> 00:49:47,710
Yes. You are right.

685
00:49:47,710 --> 00:49:50,655
That is a fact.

686
00:49:50,655 --> 00:49:52,114
Still...

687
00:49:52,114 --> 00:49:57,483
I didn't think it was right for all
that noise and criticism either.

688
00:49:57,483 --> 00:49:59,632
There was also what Joon said too.

689
00:50:02,512 --> 00:50:03,722
Joon?

690
00:50:04,742 --> 00:50:06,144
What did she say?

691
00:50:06,144 --> 00:50:10,432
Whether you make
a statement or not, that's up to you.

692
00:50:10,432 --> 00:50:15,840
However, shouldn't you go and tell the
truth about why that happened that day?

693
00:50:21,932 --> 00:50:23,076
Joon?

694
00:50:24,744 --> 00:50:26,014
For me?

695
00:50:27,036 --> 00:50:29,016
For me?

696
00:50:29,016 --> 00:50:31,670
The thing that really offended
me and made me angry...

697
00:50:31,670 --> 00:50:33,500
was that no one
gave me a sincere apology.

698
00:50:33,500 --> 00:50:37,445
It was your attitude
of trying cover it up with money.

699
00:50:37,445 --> 00:50:40,501
And? What else did Joon say?

700
00:50:40,501 --> 00:50:42,942
Did she have any other worries about me?

701
00:50:42,942 --> 00:50:44,570
I'm begging you, please.

702
00:50:44,570 --> 00:50:49,344
If there's anything else you can recall,
please tell me anything, all of it.

703
00:50:51,152 --> 00:50:53,059
Are you sure you're not a pervert?

704
00:50:53,059 --> 00:50:54,199
What?

705
00:50:57,161 --> 00:50:58,436
Oh!

706
00:51:04,847 --> 00:51:07,000
I'm not. It's a misunderstanding again.

707
00:51:07,000 --> 00:51:10,311
I don't know why
this keeps happening to me.

708
00:51:11,599 --> 00:51:13,943
I'm very sorry for this misunderstanding.

709
00:51:13,943 --> 00:51:16,507
Please don't tell Joon.

710
00:51:16,509 --> 00:51:19,286
Gosh, seriously. I ought to just...

711
00:51:22,326 --> 00:51:25,039
Ah... Mother.

712
00:51:25,039 --> 00:51:27,059
Hello.

713
00:51:27,059 --> 00:51:28,181
Mother?

714
00:51:34,552 --> 00:51:36,862
Mother? Whose mother?

715
00:51:36,862 --> 00:51:38,590
Who else? Joon's mother.

716
00:51:38,590 --> 00:51:40,891
Oh, really?

717
00:51:40,891 --> 00:51:42,018
Is she out of money again?

718
00:51:42,018 --> 00:51:43,402
Money?

719
00:51:43,402 --> 00:51:46,182
Every time Joon's about to save
money, she comes and takes it all.

720
00:51:46,182 --> 00:51:47,625
Then she comes again and again.

721
00:51:47,625 --> 00:51:48,807
What?

722
00:51:48,807 --> 00:51:52,135
Why? Why would a parent
take their child's money?

723
00:51:52,135 --> 00:51:54,137
I know. That's what I'm saying...

724
00:51:56,905 --> 00:51:59,019
It's a secret that I told you this.

725
00:51:59,019 --> 00:52:01,056
Then the lingerie thing is a secret too.

726
00:52:01,057 --> 00:52:02,420
- Deal.
- Deal.

727
00:52:09,730 --> 00:52:11,543
She's here for money?

728
00:52:36,152 --> 00:52:37,222
Hey!

729
00:52:38,692 --> 00:52:41,652
Who said you could put this garbage here?

730
00:52:41,652 --> 00:52:43,603
Seriously, so annoying!

731
00:52:43,603 --> 00:52:46,173
Sorry. I'm sorry, Sir.

732
00:52:46,173 --> 00:52:47,355
Move!

733
00:52:47,355 --> 00:52:48,429
Sorry.

734
00:52:48,429 --> 00:52:50,815
Don't do anything
you have to be sorry for then.

735
00:53:15,155 --> 00:53:17,701
<i>Joon, your mom is here.</i>

736
00:53:57,257 --> 00:53:59,146
You're just getting home? You're late.

737
00:54:07,746 --> 00:54:10,277
You should've called
if you ran out of side dishes.

738
00:54:10,277 --> 00:54:13,065
All the food in your fridge
was instant food.

739
00:54:13,065 --> 00:54:15,179
I told you that
I can't get you that money.

740
00:54:16,628 --> 00:54:18,530
Do you think I'm here for money?

741
00:54:18,530 --> 00:54:20,219
I came to see your face.

742
00:54:22,648 --> 00:54:24,675
Why are you doing this to me?

743
00:54:24,675 --> 00:54:26,500
Did you leave some
money of yours with me?

744
00:54:26,500 --> 00:54:28,788
Or did I borrow money from you, Mom?

745
00:54:28,788 --> 00:54:31,038
Why are always coming
to me with your hand out?

746
00:54:32,802 --> 00:54:35,673
Eat up. It's your favorite, potato stew.

747
00:54:35,673 --> 00:54:39,574
I really think I'm going to go
insane whenever you do this.

748
00:54:39,574 --> 00:54:40,784
Do you know that?

749
00:54:40,784 --> 00:54:43,784
I never asked you for money,
even when I was in school.

750
00:54:43,784 --> 00:54:47,286
After I graduated high school,
I did everything on my own.

751
00:54:47,286 --> 00:54:49,784
What did you do for me
that you're acting like this?

752
00:54:49,784 --> 00:54:52,724
Why do you show up
so brazen with no shame?

753
00:54:52,724 --> 00:54:55,536
How can you hold your hand out to me?

754
00:54:55,536 --> 00:55:00,923
I don't even expect a mom
that I can rely on in my life.

755
00:55:00,923 --> 00:55:05,076
At least, stop expecting
things from me, would you?

756
00:55:06,443 --> 00:55:09,224
I said stop doing that!

757
00:55:11,255 --> 00:55:13,507
Eat your rice.

758
00:55:13,507 --> 00:55:16,175
Let's eat. I'm hungry.

759
00:55:35,735 --> 00:55:37,099
I'm sorry.

760
00:55:39,181 --> 00:55:40,742
I'm a bad mom.

761
00:55:46,920 --> 00:55:48,030
Mom.

762
00:55:51,385 --> 00:55:54,275
I really dont have 10 million won.

763
00:55:56,065 --> 00:55:58,215
Yes, I know.

764
00:55:58,215 --> 00:56:00,141
Just eat your rice.

765
00:56:37,422 --> 00:56:39,036
What are you doing?

766
00:56:43,018 --> 00:56:44,208
Sit down.

767
00:56:46,775 --> 00:56:48,030
Why were you there?

768
00:56:48,030 --> 00:56:50,603
Why are you always
hanging around Joon's place?

769
00:56:51,849 --> 00:56:53,125
One moment, Jae Hoon.

770
00:57:02,260 --> 00:57:05,273
Jae Hoon, do you happen
to have 10 million won?

771
00:57:07,981 --> 00:57:09,211
What are you talking about?

772
00:57:09,211 --> 00:57:11,019
Why do you suddenly need
10 million won?

773
00:57:14,112 --> 00:57:16,119
Honestly, the thing is...

774
00:57:18,081 --> 00:57:19,802
Joon's mother is here.

775
00:57:21,030 --> 00:57:23,961
Joon is crying.

776
00:57:24,842 --> 00:57:27,210
It's not even 1 billion won
or 100 million won.

777
00:57:27,210 --> 00:57:28,659
It's only 10 million won.

778
00:57:30,735 --> 00:57:34,547
You just got kicked out
of your house like a bum.

779
00:57:34,547 --> 00:57:35,947
Should you be worrying about Joon?

780
00:57:35,947 --> 00:57:38,556
No, no. It's the time to worry about me.

781
00:57:38,556 --> 00:57:41,478
In two or three days,
Mom will have cooked Father alive.

782
00:57:41,478 --> 00:57:43,088
Then he will have cooled down.

783
00:57:43,088 --> 00:57:46,123
That's when I'll go back naturally.

784
00:57:46,123 --> 00:57:48,943
No, that won't be long enough.

785
00:57:50,344 --> 00:57:53,114
Five days? Will it be a week?

786
00:57:53,114 --> 00:57:56,231
You can't take care of yourself
and you want 10 million won?

787
00:57:56,231 --> 00:57:57,532
What a joke.

788
00:57:58,481 --> 00:58:01,208
Joon is crying right now!

789
00:58:01,208 --> 00:58:02,592
Can't you do it?

790
00:58:04,954 --> 00:58:07,958
If you're so worried,
then look into it yourself.

791
00:58:09,838 --> 00:58:13,182
That guy is so cold.
He has no blood or tears.

792
00:58:14,344 --> 00:58:16,887
Joon is crying right now.

793
01:00:10,483 --> 01:00:14,106
Wait, how could you not have
10 million won, Mom?

794
01:00:14,106 --> 01:00:16,878
Don't be like this. I really need it.

795
01:00:16,878 --> 01:00:18,567
For real, right now.

796
01:00:18,567 --> 01:00:20,041
It's your father's orders.

797
01:00:20,041 --> 01:00:22,581
We can't give you a thing.

798
01:00:22,581 --> 01:00:23,822
Mom.

799
01:00:24,902 --> 01:00:26,985
Do you think only
your accounts are blocked?

800
01:00:26,985 --> 01:00:29,385
Mine have all been blocked
for the time being.

801
01:00:29,385 --> 01:00:31,637
<i>The combinations for the safes
have been changed too.</i>

802
01:00:31,637 --> 01:00:35,603
He says he's going to check all of
my credit card transactions.

803
01:00:35,603 --> 01:00:41,193
Unless you want to see me
get divorced, just hang up.

804
01:00:41,193 --> 01:00:42,373
Seriously...

805
01:00:54,693 --> 01:00:57,431
Se Na, it's your older brother.
Send me 10 million won.

806
01:00:58,621 --> 01:01:00,530
You heard what Mom said.

807
01:01:00,530 --> 01:01:02,320
Can't you see what's going on?

808
01:01:02,320 --> 01:01:06,411
If I give you 10 won,
Dad said he'll kick me out too.

809
01:01:06,411 --> 01:01:09,349
If you don't want to see a divorce
and me getting kicked out too

810
01:01:09,349 --> 01:01:11,135
please get it together, okay?

811
01:01:19,907 --> 01:01:23,360
Is this for real, a true story? Huh?

812
01:01:26,802 --> 01:01:28,882
That measly 10 million won.

813
01:01:28,882 --> 01:01:30,974
It's not even much.
Why's everyone being this way?

814
01:01:32,141 --> 01:01:34,780
It may be a measly 10 million won to you.

815
01:01:34,780 --> 01:01:38,471
To some, it's big money that they may
or may not be able to save in a year.

816
01:01:40,878 --> 01:01:42,429
You really don't have 10 million won?

817
01:01:46,081 --> 01:01:48,469
I barely managed to get you your phone.

818
01:01:48,469 --> 01:01:50,155
Be thankful for that.

819
01:02:00,960 --> 01:02:03,436
So cold, so cold, so cold.

820
01:02:06,864 --> 01:02:09,277
<i>Hyuk! I saw the news.</i>

821
01:02:09,277 --> 01:02:11,313
<i>You looked great on TV.</i>

822
01:02:11,313 --> 01:02:13,244
Gosh, what does she want now?

823
01:02:26,889 --> 01:02:30,380
Hyuk, Hyuk, Hyuk!

824
01:02:30,380 --> 01:02:32,923
Hyuk! Oh, Hyuk!

825
01:02:34,329 --> 01:02:37,809
Seriously, you look
like you suffered so much.

826
01:02:37,809 --> 01:02:41,490
Do you know how worried Chae Ri
was when she couldn't reach you?

827
01:02:41,490 --> 01:02:42,539
Yes.

828
01:02:44,329 --> 01:02:47,510
Let's calm down and let me
ask you for a favor.

829
01:02:47,510 --> 01:02:48,851
Ask me for anything.

830
01:02:48,851 --> 01:02:50,568
Lend me 10 million won.

831
01:02:54,481 --> 01:02:56,139
I need it urgently.

832
01:02:56,139 --> 01:02:58,639
Lend me 10 million won.

833
01:02:58,639 --> 01:03:01,128
Hyuk, I understand you're mad at me.

834
01:03:01,128 --> 01:03:02,659
You're wrong about that day.

835
01:03:02,659 --> 01:03:05,798
I've forgotten about that day and
I have nothing to be mad about.

836
01:03:05,798 --> 01:03:07,998
So, just that 10 million won.

837
01:03:07,998 --> 01:03:12,059
Look, I get that you're mad.

838
01:03:12,059 --> 01:03:14,708
How could you ask
to break up in such a dirty way?

839
01:03:14,708 --> 01:03:16,278
What are you talking about?

840
01:03:16,278 --> 01:03:18,099
We are already broken up.

841
01:03:18,099 --> 01:03:20,545
Since when? When did we break up?

842
01:03:20,545 --> 01:03:22,704
I never broke up with you.

843
01:03:23,764 --> 01:03:26,315
Chae Ri... Chae Ri!

844
01:03:26,315 --> 01:03:29,795
No matter how unreasonable
you're being, this is not right.

845
01:03:29,795 --> 01:03:33,036
Sung Kyu is my friend.

846
01:03:33,036 --> 01:03:36,367
Does Sung Kyu know you're doing this?

847
01:03:36,367 --> 01:03:39,184
Sung Kyu and I are not in a relationship.

848
01:03:39,184 --> 01:03:42,264
It was all a misunderstanding that day.

849
01:03:42,264 --> 01:03:45,476
That's the bag that I bought you, right?

850
01:03:46,856 --> 01:03:49,416
I remember it being worth
more than 10 million won.

851
01:03:49,416 --> 01:03:52,456
If you don't want to give
me money, give that back to me.

852
01:03:55,463 --> 01:03:57,014
No, you can't!

853
01:03:59,349 --> 01:04:00,750
You're crazy.

854
01:04:02,130 --> 01:04:05,222
I really don't like
your personality today.

855
01:04:05,222 --> 01:04:06,869
Contact me once you feel better.

856
01:04:06,869 --> 01:04:09,193
No matter how mad you are, this is wrong.

857
01:04:19,858 --> 01:04:21,052
What a waste.

858
01:04:50,869 --> 01:04:52,063
Are you doing well?

859
01:04:58,599 --> 01:05:01,114
Your account matures in a month
and you're going to close it?

860
01:05:01,114 --> 01:05:05,143
If you close it now,
you won't get much interest.

861
01:05:05,143 --> 01:05:07,943
It won't amount to much anyway.

862
01:05:07,943 --> 01:05:09,786
- Please do it.
- Okay.

863
01:05:22,146 --> 01:05:23,277
Woo Sung!

864
01:05:28,795 --> 01:05:29,862
Hyuk.

865
01:05:31,378 --> 01:05:32,389
Are you okay?

866
01:05:32,389 --> 01:05:34,556
Yeah, I suppose.

867
01:05:34,556 --> 01:05:37,179
I was about to go
for a lunch appointment.

868
01:05:37,179 --> 01:05:38,539
I'll cancel it. Let's go eat.

869
01:05:38,539 --> 01:05:40,443
No, Woo Sung. I don't need to eat.

870
01:05:40,443 --> 01:05:43,217
Actually, I came to ask for a favor.

871
01:05:47,572 --> 01:05:49,128
Can you give me 10 million won?

872
01:05:55,625 --> 01:05:57,815
I only have 3,000 won.
Can you give me 10?

873
01:05:58,755 --> 01:06:00,556
They're for my mom.

874
01:06:00,556 --> 01:06:01,688
All right.

875
01:06:01,688 --> 01:06:03,418
Thank you!

876
01:06:03,418 --> 01:06:05,199
- Here you go.
- Here.

877
01:06:05,199 --> 01:06:06,639
Thank you. Sell lots.

878
01:06:06,639 --> 01:06:07,820
Come again.

879
01:06:12,331 --> 01:06:15,429
<i>To tell you the truth,
there's a girl I like.</i>

880
01:06:16,760 --> 01:06:18,659
I'm home.

881
01:06:21,018 --> 01:06:23,880
<i>She's crying over 10 million won.</i>

882
01:06:23,880 --> 01:06:27,454
<i>What is that? What is money anyway?</i>

883
01:06:27,454 --> 01:06:31,132
<i>What else can I do
for her besides money?</i>

884
01:06:31,132 --> 01:06:34,452
<i>I don't like it when she cries.</i>

885
01:06:34,452 --> 01:06:35,952
<i>Please do me this favor, Woo Sung.</i>

886
01:06:39,943 --> 01:06:42,105
<i>Make sure to eat all your meals.</i>

887
01:06:42,105 --> 01:06:45,943
<i>The young man downstairs delivered
the money you wanted to give me.</i>

888
01:06:45,943 --> 01:06:48,463
<i>Thank you, my daughter.
I'll use it well.</i>

889
01:06:58,306 --> 01:06:59,827
<i>[Mom] </i>

890
01:07:07,206 --> 01:07:10,911
Pick up. Pick up, Mom.

891
01:07:17,338 --> 01:07:19,139
<i>[My Daughter]</i>

892
01:07:19,139 --> 01:07:21,632
Hurry up and pick up, Mom.

893
01:07:21,632 --> 01:07:23,762
Please pick up, would you?

894
01:07:44,844 --> 01:07:45,978
What is it?

895
01:07:48,181 --> 01:07:50,724
Joon. What brings you here?

896
01:07:59,039 --> 01:08:01,807
Joon, why did you do that?

897
01:08:01,807 --> 01:08:03,666
Am I that much of a joke to you?

898
01:08:03,666 --> 01:08:05,628
Don't my words mean anything to you?

899
01:08:07,543 --> 01:08:09,280
What? You're born again?

900
01:08:09,280 --> 01:08:11,347
You want me to believe
that you've changed?

901
01:08:11,347 --> 01:08:14,099
What a joke.
You haven't changed one bit.

902
01:08:14,099 --> 01:08:16,237
A rude jerk to the bone,
third generation rich guy.

903
01:08:16,237 --> 01:08:18,287
A piece of crap third generation bum!

904
01:08:24,756 --> 01:08:26,063
<i>She is crying.</i>

905
01:08:27,623 --> 01:08:29,903
<i>I didn't want her to cry anymore.</i>

906
01:08:31,173 --> 01:08:33,795
<i>I only wanted to see her smile.</i>

907
01:08:35,494 --> 01:08:37,225
<i>So, what went wrong?</i>

908
01:08:39,113 --> 01:08:42,604
I don't ever want to see you again.

909
01:08:49,833 --> 01:08:52,860
<i>What am I supposed to do now?</i>

910
01:08:55,793 --> 01:09:00,793
Subtitles by DramaFever

911
01:09:17,921 --> 01:09:21,757
<i>[Revolutionary Love]</i>

912
01:09:21,757 --> 01:09:23,631
<i>How is Hyuk doing these days?</i>

913
01:09:23,631 --> 01:09:25,998
<i>You all saw that I
was kicked out in the nude, right?</i>

914
01:09:25,998 --> 01:09:28,056
<i>I need money. I need to earn it.</i>

915
01:09:28,056 --> 01:09:29,653
<i>- I agree.
- Me too.</i>

916
01:09:29,653 --> 01:09:31,545
<i>What? Hyuk's at the company?</i>

917
01:09:31,545 --> 01:09:32,686
<i>This isn't right.</i>

918
01:09:32,686 --> 01:09:34,630
<i>- You like him.
- Like him? Who?</i>

919
01:09:34,630 --> 01:09:35,993
<i>You're even cleaning now?</i>

920
01:09:35,993 --> 01:09:38,871
<i>Why are you insisting on following
her around doing hard jobs?</i>

921
01:09:38,871 --> 01:09:40,627
<i>When will I ever make all that money?</i>

922
01:09:40,627 --> 01:09:42,426
<i>I want to buy this. How do I do that?</i>

923
01:09:42,426 --> 01:09:44,390
<i>He's fallen for
some girl and can't focus.</i>

924
01:09:44,390 --> 01:09:45,640
<i>My brother has a girlfriend?</i>

925
01:09:45,640 --> 01:09:47,444
<i>You punk! What are you doing here?</i>

926
01:09:47,444 --> 01:09:49,533
<i>Catch him!</i>

